Package org.pepstock.charba.client.commons

Class ArrayDoubleList

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.pepstock.charba.client.commons.AbstractArrayList<Double,​ArrayDouble>
      • org.pepstock.charba.client.commons.ArrayDoubleList
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    Iterable<Double>, Collection<Double>, List<Double>
    public final class ArrayDoubleList
extends AbstractArrayList<Double,​ArrayDouble>
    The user of this interface has precise control over where in the list each element is inserted.
    The user can access elements by their integer index (position in the list), and search for elements in the list.
    This implementation uses a java script object as back-end to store objects (doubles).
    Author:
    Andrea "Stock" Stocchero
